elogind (239.1~rc2-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * upstream rc2
  * Rules: reenable debug with -Ddebug-extra, following systemd upstream
  * Ship libelogind-dev's man pages into the new libelogind-doc package:
     this is to avoid conflict with libsystemd-dev man pages and allow
     for parallel install of libsystemd-dev and libelogind-dev
  * turn elogind's Depends on Sysv | runit-init  into a Pre-Depends
  * elogind-sysv:
     - add a sysv-elogind symlink to elogind
     - use the sysv-elogind symlink to check whether the
       sysv-elogind package is installed and prevent the sysv
       script from starting in case it's not
  *  add lintian override for 'binaries-have-file-conflict' (elogind-sysv|run)
  *  Clean up for itp:
     - removing comments and old code from rules
     - removing Breaks and Replaces that are only relevant locally from control
     - removing some old files in contrib/
     - removing old patches dir patches/old
     - remove the TODO file
     - remove the README.Debian
     - removing duplicates-filed section and priority in control
     - redirect output of update.rc.d to /dev/null in elogind-sysv maintscript
     - bump Standards Version to 4.2.1: add 'Rules-Requires-Root: no' and
       set debhelper >=10.4 as a build-dependency

 -- Lorenzo Puliti <lorenzo.ru.g@gmail.com>  Thu, 27 Sep 2018 10:18:07 +0200

elogind (239.1~rc1-2) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Buildflags: replace local with Debian standard buildflags;
     this mean remove -march=core2  (will not work on older
     processors still supported by Debian) and readd -g (this
     fix lintian debug-file-with-no-debug-symbols)
  * libelogind-dev: move man pages into man3-e to avoid conflicts
     with libsystemd-dev man pages
  * rules: disable debug

